      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Small field but good race. HEBEL (2) last appeared three weeks ago over 1400m at Alice Springs when he finished second. This is his first run for the Terry Gillett stable. In great form and with the claim looks a top chance. BEAU FACTOR (1) is a seasoned sprinter back in winning form scoring over a mile in Alice last time. Back in trip but is course and distance placed and will be tough to stop. ANKLE ROLEX (3) is hard to fault winning the last three on end. Six-length winner here last time and goes in everything. ANECDOTAL (6) has been kept fresh since a dominant five-length win when leading through latest. Up a kilo but looks the leader and will take catching again. FIELDS OF COURAGE (4) was runner-up behind ANECDOTAL latest and can only be fitter. Can run well again.",
